    <description>Plants to 60 cm. Stems: pseudobulbs slightly spaced, ovoid to ellipsoid, usually
        elongate, flattened, 3–15 × 1–3.5 cm. Leaves 1–3, oblong-lanceolate to linear-lanceolate,
        5–40 × 1–6 cm. Inflorescences racemes, rarely paniculate, pedunculate, elongate, loosely
        few-flowered, to 45 cm, base with 1 or 2 spathes. Flowers not resupinate, successive,
        usually 3–4 open at a time, sometimes with capsules present, green to yellowish green with a
        few purplish spots near base; sepals and petals similar, hanging, twisted,
        linear-lanceolate, 25–35 × 3–6 mm; lip deep purple, orbiculate-cordate, concave, 1.2–2.3 ×
        1.5–3 mm, base whitish marked with conspicuous purple veins, calli 2, yellowish,
        cushionlike, apex sharply mu-cronate; anthers 3, middle anther with 4 pollinia, laterals
        with 2 each, orange; column short, stout, 6–10 mm, apex 5-toothed. Capsules 2–4 × 0.8–1.5
        cm.</description>
